An injury or health problem was the reason for the contact.<br/>Heavy bleeding had not occurred in the previous 2 hours.<br/>An illness or health problem was the main problem.<br/>User Comments: TEST<br/>The individual was not fighting for breath.<br/>The main reason for the assessment was not an allergic reaction, heart attack, chest/upper back pain, probable stroke, recent fit/seizure or suicide attempt.<br/>The main reason for contact was not new confusion, declared diabetic hypo/hyperglycaemia, or ICD shock.<br/>The skin on the torso felt normal, warm or hot.<br/>Pathway selected - Nosebleeds without Injury<br/>The individual was not feeling faint or dizzy.<br/>The nose was continuing to bleed.<br/>There was no nasal foreign body.<br/>Constant pressure had been applied to the soft part of the nose for at least 10 minutes.<br/>Instructions given were: The individual needs to attend a treatment centre within 1 hour.<br/>Directory of Services referral: **TESTING ONLY** DO NOT SEND PATIENTS - ED Test Service for EDDI<br/>Advice given: Worsening <br/>
